reviews.text: Absolutely SHOCKING behaviour from member of platform staff today. Young lady with young baby, buggy, baby bag and suitcase, very wet and lost, asked if there was any way to get to the other platform was rudely told ' No, use the stairs' when she politely asked if the man could help her with her baby and things you was curtly informed 'l don't do that' and he turned his back on her. The poor girl was left in tears and no way to get even to another station with a lift or disabled acces. I called a cab for her and her mother arranged to meet her and get her home. I am APPALLED at the callous way she was treated and the fact that she was obviously distressed, anything could have happened!
convenient local station but could be maintained better

Nice local station easy parking and cycle storage, has a off station snack van does sausage sandwiches bacon rolls tea and coffee etc, and Indian restaurant if you fancy a curry and cold beer after a long week.

Very small station, manned less and less these days, but at least it's kept clean and tidy. hoever, the waiting areas need some serious work, and the facilities are basicly non existant. Things not to look for: phones, shops, toilets for more than one person at a time, or an ATM. but at least you can get a taxi some times.

A typical small town station with a limited hours ticket office, though there's a ticket machine outside the main entrance. Parking and bike storage is available. It does have a good Indian restaurant attached if you're interested.
